      • imag

      • length

        public double length
        The magnitude of this complex number, or, equivalently, the length of this number interpreted as a vector.

        If real or imag is modified directly, this field may become incorrect. In such a scenario, updateMembers() must be called before any other methods from this class are called, otherwise the resulting complex numbers may be inaccurate as well.

        See Also:
        real, imag, updateMembers()

      • lengthSquared

        public double lengthSquared
        The magnitude of this complex number, squared.

        This field exists solely for convenience.

        If real or imag is modified directly, this field may become incorrect. In such a scenario, updateMembers() must be called before any other methods from this class are called, otherwise the resulting complex numbers may be inaccurate as well.

        See Also:
        real, imag, updateMembers()

      • arg

        public double arg
        The argument of this complex number, or, in other words, the angle this number (as a vector) makes with the positive-real axis on the complex coordinate plane.

        If real or imag is modified directly, this field may become incorrect. In such a scenario, updateMembers() must be called before any other methods from this class are called, otherwise the resulting complex numbers may be inaccurate as well.

        See Also:
        real, imag, updateMembers()

      • updateMembers

        @Contract(value="-> this")
 @NotNull
public @NotNull ComplexDouble updateMembers()
        Update this ComplexDouble's instance variables to be in sync with each other.

        This method is primarily for use after a ComplexDouble is modified directly via its instance vars real and imag. In such a scenario, calling this method will force the ComplexDouble to update its values of length, lengthSquared, and arg to correspond to the same imaginary number represented by real and imag.

        Returns:
        This ComplexDouble, after the forced update
        See Also:
        real, imag, length, lengthSquared, arg

      • round

        @Contract(value="-> this")
 @NotNull
public @NotNull ComplexDouble round()
        Independently rounds the real and imaginary components of this ComplexNumber if each is within a specified threshold of an integer.

        This functionality is identical to FastMath.round(float, float) and FastMath.round(double, double).

        This implementation rounds with a threshold of 10-10.

        Specified by:
        round in interface ComplexNumber<ComplexDouble>
        Returns:
        This ComplexNumber, after rounding
        See Also:

      • normalize

        @Contract(value="-> this")
 @NotNull
public @NotNull ComplexDouble normalize()
